    rationale: "In sensorineural hearing loss: the Weber lateralizes to the GOOD ear (right, in this case), confirming the left ear is the affected side. The Rinne test on the left shows AC > BC (positive Rinne), which is technically normal \u2014 but both are reduced in absolute volume. This is the classic sensorineural pattern: the Rinne remains positive because the conductive pathway is intact, but overall hearing is diminished due to cochlear or CN VIII damage. A negative Rinne (BC > AC) would indicate conductive loss. The Weber lateralizing to the right rules out right-sided pathology.",
    metadata: { topic: "audiology", priority: "high" },
