    rationale: "In conductive hearing loss, the external or middle ear pathway is blocked, reducing air-conducted sound. Bone conduction bypasses this block and reaches the cochlea directly. Therefore, bone conduction appears relatively better than air conduction \u2014 a negative Rinne (BC > AC). In normal hearing and sensorineural loss, air conduction is greater than bone conduction (positive Rinne) because the ossicular chain amplifies air-conducted sound. A negative Rinne is pathognomonic of a conductive block in that ear and should prompt investigation of the external canal, tympanic membrane, and middle ear.",
