    rationale: "In optic neuropathies including optic neuritis, color vision deficits \u2014 particularly red-green discrimination errors on Ishihara plates \u2014 often appear before significant visual acuity loss. This is because the papillomacular bundle fibers carrying color information are among the first affected by demyelination. Missing 6 of 14 plates represents a significant color vision deficit and confirms active optic nerve dysfunction. Color errors are not a sign of retinal disease specifically; they are a hallmark of optic nerve pathology. There is no threshold of acuity loss required before color vision is affected.",
